        "title": "Split context tests out of clawsweeper suite",
        "body": "episode 1 in a series on making clawsweeper tests not mostly a 20,000 line file, which breaks syntax highlighting and slows down models\n\n## Summary\n- move GitHub context-window and prior-review parsing coverage into `test/context.test.ts`\n- move close-decision, close-reason, and related PR-reference coverage into `test/close-reasons.test.ts`\n- add `test/helpers.ts` for shared test setup helpers instead of duplicating them across split files\n- remove the moved tests and unused imports from `test/clawsweeper.test.ts`\n- update `AGENTS.md` to steer future tests into narrower files\n\n## Tests\n- `node --test test/context.test.ts test/clawsweeper.test.ts`\n- `node --test --test-name-pattern 'media proof preparation|invalid close semantics|referencingMergedPullRequestsForIssue' test/clawsweeper.test.ts test/close-reasons.test.ts`\\n- `pnpm exec oxlint test/clawsweeper.test.ts test/close-reasons.test.ts test/helpers.ts --deny-warnings --report-unused-disable-directives -D correctness`\\n- `pnpm run check`",
